Add a parameter to the rss macro for an xsl file to transform the xml. 

{rss:url=http://rss.news.yahoo.com/rss/stocks\|max=5|xsl=http://www.somedomain.com/directory/transformrss.xsl}

We use the rss standard as the format for a lot of the data we display on our intranet and transform it using xsl.  That way we might just show the titles, or bold the title, or make it a bulleted list, and so forth.  

Having the ability to transform the rss xml with xsl would give great flexibility to the presentation of external data in the wiki.

Alternatively, it might be better to have a new macro which allows any xml source, not just RSS, with an xsl file.

